title: Website title
card-err-head: Title of the error message when a check failed to start, used on the main page
card-err-desc: The error message when a check failed to start, used on the main page
card-about-head: Title of the about panel on the main page
card-about-desc1: Content of the about panel on the main page
card-about-desc2: Content of the about panel on the main page
card-about-desc3: Content of the about panel on the main page. Remember to replace the link with the corresponding one of your language's Wikipedia
tbl-h-conn: Table header of project connectivity (based on round-trip time a.k.a. ping)
tbl-h-block: Table header of whether user can edit a project or not
footer-code:
The source code link located at the bottom of the site.
It points to https://github.com/diskdance/wscd
footer-license:
The license link located at the bottom of the site.
It points to https://github.com/diskdance/wscd/blob/master/LICENSE
header-slogan: Slogan text located at top of the page
name-key-missing: Fallback name when a friendly name for a project cannot be found
avl-yes: Text indicating that a project is available
avl-no: Text indicating that a project is unavailable
blk-yes: Text indicating that the user is blocked from editing a project
blk-no: Text indicating that the user is able to edit a project
blk-unknown: Text indicating that whether the user is able to edit the project cannot be determined
blk-non-wiki: Text indicating that this project is not a wiki, e.g. diff.wikimedia.org
pending: Text indicating that a project is yet to be checked
checking: Text indicated that a check is in progress
rtt-excellent: Text indicating that the connectivity is excellent (very good), or the round-trip time (ping) is extremely low
rtt-good: Text indicating that the connectivity is good, or the round-trip time (ping) is low
rtt-bad: Text indicating that the connectivity is bad, or the round-trip time (ping) is high
rtt-title:
Exact round-trip time a.k.a. ping in milliseconds.
This is displayed as tooltip of connectivity field
ct-field-ext-check: Text indicating that this check would be an extended check (all Wikimedia domains are checked), displayed as alt text for the ToggleSwitch on the main page
ct-field-type: Title text of the check type selection field
ct-field-std: Text indicating that this check would be a standard check (only popular Wikimedia sites are checked), displayed next to the ToggleSwitch on the main page
ct-field-ext: Text indicating that this check would be an extended check (all Wikimedia domains are checked), displayed next to the ToggleSwitch on the main page
btn-chk: Text of the blue round button on the main page
sc-chk-h: Title of the summary card when a check is in progress. $1 is replaced with already-checked domains while $2 is replaced with all domains that should be checked
sc-chk-h-err: Text of the title of the summary card when a check is in progress and issues are found. $1 is replaced with already-checked domains while $2 is replaced with all domains that should be checked
sc-chk-desc: Descriptive text in the summary card when a check is in progress
sc-chk-cur: Descriptive text indicating the currently checking domain
sc-end-h-np: Title of the summary card when no issues are found at last
sc-end-b-np: Descriptive text of the summary card when no issues are found at last
sc-end-h-err: Title of the summary card when issues are found after the check
sc-end-b-err: Descriptive text of the summary card when issues are found after the check
sc-end-b-err-1t: Descriptive text of the summary card when issues are found after the check
sc-end-b-err-1p1: Descriptive text of the summary card when issues are found after the check
sc-end-b-err-1p2: Descriptive text of the summary card when issues are found after the check
sc-end-b-err-1p3: Descriptive text of the summary card when issues are found after the check
sc-end-b-err-2t: Descriptive text of the summary card when issues are found after the check
sc-end-b-err-2p1: Descriptive text of the summary card when issues are found after the check
sc-end-b-err-2p2: Descriptive text of the summary card when issues are found after the check. Remember to replace the link with the corresponding one of your language's Wikipedia
sc-inaccessible: Descriptive text with $1 replaced with inaccessible/unavailable domains
sc-blocked: Descriptive text with $1 replaced with uneditable/blocked domains
sc-domain-desc: Outline of a list of domains, e.g. en.wikipedia.org and 2 more
sc-domain-desc-none: Text displayed when no domains are inaccessible or uneditable
sc-btn-hide: Text of the button to collapse the check data table
sc-btn-show: Text of the button to expand the check data table
sc-btn-recheck: Text of the button to re-run the check
sc-btn-dl: Text of the button to download check data
